messages.content:
Based on the job description {{20.result}}and the candidate's resume. Your task is to analyze both and determine how well the resume matches the job description. Consider key aspects such as skills, experience, and job requirements. The output should ONLY be a number for the job match. (ex. 70)

And since resume is too long, below is the candidate summary for Job Match Comparison.

 ```1. Candidate All Skills List: Frontend Technologies: React, TypeScript, NextJS, Redux, Cypress, Jest, React Testing Library, Webpack, Babel.Backend & API Development: Node.js, Python, Java, C#, GraphQL, SQL Server.Cloud Technologies: AWS Services (Glue, Lambda, S3, DynamoDB, CloudFormation, API Gateway, Amplify, AppSync, CloudWatch), Azure Durable Functions, Azure DevOps.Testing & Automation: Cypress (E2E Testing), Jest, xUnit.Collaboration & Tools: Postman, PowerBI, OAuth, CI/CD pipelines, AWS and Microsoft internal tools.Accessibility: WCAG/ADA-compliant applications.Productivity Enhancements: UI component libraries, performance optimization, and integration improvements. 2. Summaries of Work Experience: Amazon Web Services (AWS) (Oct 2022 - Present)As a Software Engineer II, spearheaded the development of the Glue Studio Connector Framework, improving delivery speed by 50%. Enhanced the ETL workflow editor for large datasets, reducing page load times by 20% and customer UI issues by 15%. Led the creation of a reusable UI component library, accelerating feature delivery by 30% while improving accessibility and security. Actively mentored team members and collaborated across teams to ensure alignment and code quality.Microsoft (Oct 2021 - Oct 2022)Designed and implemented the breakout room functionality in Microsoft Teams, enhancing virtual meeting productivity. Improved cross-application integrations within the Microsoft ecosystem, increasing user engagement. Delivered ADA/WCAG-compliant applications, raised test coverage by 20%, and fostered engineering excellence through mentorship, code reviews, and testing automation.Clir Renewables (Jan 2021 – Oct 2021)Developed features to streamline the home-moving experience for customers, working closely with UX designers to create reusable components and custom solutions. Collaborated with Product Managers to plan and deliver impactful product features. Significantly improved test coverage from 20% to 98% using Cypress and Jest, ensuring higher application reliability and quality.```
